<HEADLINE>
TAIWAN ICDF HELPS ENHANCE ALLIES' ICT ABILITIES: FOREIGN MINISTER
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, May 16 (CNA) 05/16/07  22:53:02 (By T.C. Jiang)
</P>
<P>
Minister of Foreign Affairs James Huang said Wednesday that
Taiwan's information and communications technology (ICT) industry
plays a vital role in the world and that the International
Cooperation and Development Fund (Taiwan ICDF) has helped enhance
the ICT abilities of the country's allies.
</P>
<P>
Huang, who is also the chairman of Taiwan ICDF, made the remarks
at an international symposium marking the inauguration of the
Taiwan ICT Alliance (TICTA).
</P>
<P>
In recent years, Taiwan's ICT industry has continued to develop,
Huang said.
</P>
<P>
Quoting a report released by the World Economic Forum (WEF) on
global information technology 2004-2005, Huang said Taiwan's ICT
industry ranks fourth in Asia and 15th in the world.
</P>
<P>
Over 50 percent of the core facilities of the world's IC, IT,
flat panel display and telecommunications factories are
manufactured in Taiwan, Huang said.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan's mobile phone penetration rate has reached 100.7 percent,
the highest in the world, while the number of local broadband
household users is approximately 4 million, representing the
world's fifth-highest penetration rate, Huang noted.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan ICDF has carried out over 30 ICT assistance projects in
recent years, according to Taiwan ICDF Secretary-General Chen
Cheng-chung.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to help from an association of information and
telecommunication manufacturers, academic researchers and private
companies, Taiwan ICDF has come up with projects tailored to the
political, economic and social development situations of Taiwan's
allies, Chen added.
</P>
